WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:02.360
Do you fear death?

00:00:02.360 --> 00:00:04.240
No I don't. Not at all.

00:00:04.240 --> 00:00:05.760
I look forward to it.

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:07.520
I don't look forward to the act of dying.

00:00:07.520 --> 00:00:08.480
But I look forward to

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:10.080
what's on the other side.

00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:11.640
And I'll mention in this context

00:00:11.640 --> 00:00:12.600
that my partner,

00:00:12.600 --> 00:00:14.200
my partner of 25 years

00:00:14.200 --> 00:00:15.960
is Christina Hardy.

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:18.320
She died last spring.

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:20.200
She was a psycho, not like myself.

00:00:20.200 --> 00:00:22.880
She had had many deep experiences.

00:00:22.880 --> 00:00:24.800
She had no fear of death.

00:00:24.800 --> 00:00:27.280
And the two of us have no fear of death

00:00:27.280 --> 00:00:28.560
because she had gone

00:00:28.560 --> 00:00:29.880
to where she would be going

00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:30.960
when she died.

00:00:30.960 --> 00:00:33.040
She had personal familiarity with it,

00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:34.280
and she knew

00:00:34.280 --> 00:00:36.360
that it was a place of great blessing,

00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:38.640
great beauty, great joy.

00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:40.680
When you understand,

00:00:40.680 --> 00:00:41.760
I mean, and I don't mean

00:00:41.760 --> 00:00:43.440
just intellectually,

00:00:43.440 --> 00:00:44.680
but understand

00:00:44.680 --> 00:00:47.680
and have had deep communion

00:00:48.120 --> 00:00:50.640
with these deeper levels of reality

00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:52.600
that on the other side of

00:00:52.600 --> 00:00:54.000
time, space, reality,

00:00:54.960 --> 00:00:57.160
then approaching death

00:00:57.160 --> 00:00:57.760
is not

00:00:57.760 --> 00:01:00.120
the dirge of sadness or mourning,

00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:03.440
or just grief and loss, but rather

00:01:03.440 --> 00:01:05.280
it becomes a celebration of a life

00:01:05.280 --> 00:01:06.560
well lived.

00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:08.760
Christina had lived her life very well.

00:01:08.760 --> 00:01:09.480
She had risen

00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:11.520
to the challenges of her life

00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:13.440
and her last years with me

00:01:13.440 --> 00:01:14.960
were some of the best years

00:01:14.960 --> 00:01:16.280
of our marriage.

00:01:16.280 --> 00:01:19.600
As we as we move towards her death.

00:01:20.920 --> 00:01:24.000
And I expect that to be true for me, too.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:26.040
I don't have any fear of death.

00:01:26.040 --> 00:01:29.040
And, in fact, I just have to be patient.

00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:31.960
Because for me,

00:01:31.960 --> 00:01:34.200
my belief is, my understanding

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:38.040
is that at the very least, when I die,

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:40.480
I'll be able to go back to

00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:42.720
some of the deepest places

00:01:42.720 --> 00:01:45.400
in the universe that I had access through

00:01:45.400 --> 00:01:46.920
my psychedelic work,

00:01:46.920 --> 00:01:48.880
because I know the address,

00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:50.760
as Robert Monroe would say,

00:01:50.760 --> 00:01:51.960
you can go anywhere

00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:53.280
where you know the address,

00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:55.640
and I know the address of these places,

00:01:55.640 --> 00:01:58.440
and I can go back to there, and I know

00:01:58.440 --> 00:01:59.400
I'll be able to go on

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:01.560
even deeper from there.

00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:04.440
So, no, I have no fear of death at all.

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:16.720
Okay, Chris, welcome to the show.

00:02:16.720 --> 00:02:20.480
Night between 1979 and 1999,

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:22.520
shortly after starting your career

00:02:22.520 --> 00:02:24.240
as a university professor,

00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:27.240
you decided to take LSD 73 times

00:02:27.520 --> 00:02:28.920
in a carefully planned,

00:02:28.920 --> 00:02:31.920
therapeutically structured sessions.

00:02:32.280 --> 00:02:33.240
And just, you know,

00:02:33.240 --> 00:02:34.440
I have to start the conversation

00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:36.040
by asking, you know, why?

00:02:36.040 --> 00:02:37.440
And and what motivated this?

00:02:37.440 --> 00:02:39.360
This is a very

00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:42.600
this is a very unique, experiment

00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:43.720
to, to put yourself through.

00:02:43.720 --> 00:02:44.960
So can you give me just share

00:02:44.960 --> 00:02:47.560
share a bit about that. Yeah.

00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:50.040
Well, I had just finished graduate school

00:02:50.040 --> 00:02:51.120
at Brown University.

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:52.200
I was a philosopher.

00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:52.680
Religion.

00:02:52.680 --> 00:02:55.320
I was starting my teaching career,

00:02:55.320 --> 00:02:58.200
and in the first year I met

00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:01.080
Ian Stevenson's work on reincarnation.

00:03:01.080 --> 00:03:04.080
That was a major pivot in my thinking.

00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:05.680
But more importantly,

00:03:05.680 --> 00:03:07.120
I met Stan Groves work.

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:07.440
I read

00:03:07.440 --> 00:03:09.040
realms of the Human Unconscious,

00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:10.280
which had just been published

00:03:10.280 --> 00:03:11.600
a couple of years before,

00:03:12.640 --> 00:03:14.160
and I immediately saw the

00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:15.680
importance of standards work

00:03:15.680 --> 00:03:17.600
not just for psychology

00:03:17.600 --> 00:03:20.240
and clinical therapeutic work,

00:03:20.240 --> 00:03:21.720
but also for my field

00:03:21.720 --> 00:03:23.520
philosophy religion.

00:03:23.520 --> 00:03:25.720
If what Stan was saying is true,

00:03:25.720 --> 00:03:27.280
then this was a methodology

00:03:27.280 --> 00:03:28.120
that would allow us

00:03:28.120 --> 00:03:29.760
to actually push

00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:30.400
the boundaries

00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:33.960
of consciousness systematically and glean

00:03:33.960 --> 00:03:36.960
philosophical insights into the structure

00:03:37.080 --> 00:03:40.560
of at least consciousness, and probably

00:03:41.120 --> 00:03:42.560
reality, that

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:43.720
the actual reality

00:03:43.720 --> 00:03:46.320
that consciousness is perceiving.

00:03:46.320 --> 00:03:49.320
So I knew this work

00:03:49.320 --> 00:03:50.640
had to be done personally.

00:03:50.640 --> 00:03:51.520
It couldn't be done

00:03:51.520 --> 00:03:54.320
well from second hand accounts.

00:03:54.320 --> 00:03:57.120
So I began this work, and I didn't

00:03:57.120 --> 00:04:00.120
expect it to last 20 years when I did it.

00:04:00.160 --> 00:04:01.200
But that's what happened.

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:03.120
I worked for four years,

00:04:03.120 --> 00:04:04.760
I stopped for six years,

00:04:04.760 --> 00:04:06.240
and then I worked for another

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:07.920
ten years very intensely.

00:04:09.240 --> 00:04:11.680
And I chose to work

00:04:11.680 --> 00:04:13.720
in with high doses of LSD.

00:04:13.720 --> 00:04:15.760
Stan outlined in his early writings

00:04:15.760 --> 00:04:17.600
two protocols that they had used.

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:19.080
One was low dose psycho

00:04:19.080 --> 00:04:20.320
lytic therapy,

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:20.720
healing

00:04:20.720 --> 00:04:21.880
those psyche away

00:04:21.880 --> 00:04:24.520
gradually layer by layer.

00:04:24.520 --> 00:04:26.240
Because of the time constraints

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:27.560
of a dual career marriage

00:04:27.560 --> 00:04:28.560
and the difficulty

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:31.640
of being able to plan a weekend

00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:35.040
for this entire session with children

00:04:35.040 --> 00:04:36.320
soon to come,

00:04:36.320 --> 00:04:39.320
I chose to work with high doses of LSD

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:41.800
in a psychedelic protocol,

00:04:41.800 --> 00:04:44.640
and I worked at 500 to 600 micrograms.

00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:45.960
And this is a regimen

00:04:45.960 --> 00:04:48.080
that I don't recommend today.

00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:49.120
I'd do it differently

00:04:49.120 --> 00:04:51.840
if I were starting over again.

00:04:51.840 --> 00:04:54.800
But basically, I thought that I could

00:04:54.800 --> 00:04:57.480
consume my karmic baggage

00:04:57.480 --> 00:04:59.440
if I just took bigger bites out of it.

00:04:59.440 --> 00:05:01.680
Working at these high doses.

00:05:01.680 --> 00:05:03.000
It turned out that I

00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:04.520
was applying a model,

00:05:06.040 --> 00:05:07.240
of psychology and a

00:05:07.240 --> 00:05:10.320
model of the human psyche that was wrong.

00:05:11.400 --> 00:05:14.360
And so because within two years,

00:05:14.360 --> 00:05:16.720
I was being drawn into experiences

00:05:16.720 --> 00:05:19.920
that were so deep and so broad, involving

00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:22.920
so many thousands of human beings,

00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:24.960
that I began to realize

00:05:24.960 --> 00:05:26.600
that my entire model

00:05:26.600 --> 00:05:29.320
of personal transformation, personal

00:05:29.320 --> 00:05:32.320
enlightenment, was too narrow,

00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:34.920
to do justice to the states

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:37.120
that actually unfold in these states.

00:05:37.120 --> 00:05:37.800
So for me,

00:05:37.800 --> 00:05:39.240
it was a professional

00:05:39.240 --> 00:05:41.600
and personal journey

00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:43.280
seeking to understand

00:05:43.280 --> 00:05:46.280
the deep structure of reality.

00:05:46.320 --> 00:05:48.320
And what was it that caused that shift

00:05:48.320 --> 00:05:51.320
from the personal to the collective?

00:05:52.120 --> 00:05:54.120
Well,

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:56.480
after about two years in the work,

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:57.400
I went through

00:05:57.400 --> 00:05:58.960
what Stan would have described

00:05:58.960 --> 00:06:01.560
as a classic ego death.

00:06:01.560 --> 00:06:03.080
Experience, culminating

00:06:03.080 --> 00:06:04.680
after two years of working

00:06:04.680 --> 00:06:05.600
at what he would call

00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:08.600
the perinatal level of consciousness,

00:06:08.760 --> 00:06:10.400
deep death.

00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:12.840
And I expected at that point

00:06:12.840 --> 00:06:14.160
for things to get easier.

00:06:14.160 --> 00:06:16.200
I expected to go more easily

00:06:16.200 --> 00:06:18.680
into transpersonal spaces.

00:06:18.680 --> 00:06:20.240
But what started immediately

00:06:20.240 --> 00:06:21.880
was a new cycle that ended

00:06:21.880 --> 00:06:23.520
up lasting another two years.

00:06:24.720 --> 00:06:26.320
I have to back up one second.

00:06:26.320 --> 00:06:27.680
My work

00:06:27.680 --> 00:06:29.880
always involved a cleansing portion

00:06:29.880 --> 00:06:30.920
of the session

00:06:30.920 --> 00:06:32.880
and an ecstatic portion of the session.

00:06:32.880 --> 00:06:35.080
So there was a purification

00:06:35.080 --> 00:06:36.840
cleansing portion

00:06:36.840 --> 00:06:38.320
which, if you'd navigated it

00:06:38.320 --> 00:06:40.920
well, would usually come to a crescendo.

00:06:40.920 --> 00:06:43.800
Some type of death and, and release.

00:06:43.800 --> 00:06:44.440
And then

00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:45.480
the rest of the session

00:06:45.480 --> 00:06:48.480
was in an ecstatic state.

00:06:48.480 --> 00:06:51.360
So in this second stage

00:06:51.360 --> 00:06:54.360
of the work, after ego death,

00:06:54.640 --> 00:06:56.400
I began to have experiences

00:06:56.400 --> 00:06:59.880
of profound human suffering, covering

00:07:00.360 --> 00:07:02.040
vast numbers of people

00:07:02.040 --> 00:07:04.120
and a vast number of years.

00:07:04.120 --> 00:07:06.960
And I was taken into it gradually

00:07:06.960 --> 00:07:08.160
but systematically.

00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:10.040
Every session was getting deeper

00:07:10.040 --> 00:07:10.720
and wider

00:07:10.720 --> 00:07:11.720
and deeper and wider,

00:07:11.720 --> 00:07:14.040
with more and more suffering.

00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:17.040
And eventually I had to realize that

00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:19.040
this was

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:20.440
larger than anything

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:22.280
that could be related to me personally.

00:07:22.280 --> 00:07:22.840
This wasn't

00:07:22.840 --> 00:07:26.400
some former life, experiences.

00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:28.520
It wasn't simply,

00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:31.760
what I wasn't drawing into

00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:32.760
my personal

00:07:32.760 --> 00:07:34.440
therapy content

00:07:34.440 --> 00:07:36.240
from the collective psyche

00:07:36.240 --> 00:07:38.960
that reinforced my personal ego death,

00:07:38.960 --> 00:07:40.400
because I really had gone

00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:41.880
through a very decisive ego

00:07:41.880 --> 00:07:45.120
death already, and that forced me.

00:07:45.120 --> 00:07:46.480
And this is the main

00:07:46.480 --> 00:07:47.640
theme of my book,

00:07:47.640 --> 00:07:51.480
Dark Nataly Dawn was to recognize

00:07:51.480 --> 00:07:53.960
that there is no strong boundary

00:07:53.960 --> 00:07:55.280
between the individual

00:07:55.280 --> 00:07:57.040
and the collective psyche,

00:07:57.040 --> 00:07:57.880
and when you work

00:07:57.880 --> 00:07:59.720
with highly energized states,

00:07:59.720 --> 00:08:03.280
as I was in using high doses of LSD,

00:08:04.200 --> 00:08:07.200
then if you work with high energy states,

00:08:07.240 --> 00:08:10.240
those energy states naturally expand

00:08:10.360 --> 00:08:13.360
to vast

00:08:13.520 --> 00:08:16.520
landscapes of the collective psyche.

00:08:16.760 --> 00:08:18.720
And literally the patient

00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:21.360
in those sessions becomes

00:08:21.360 --> 00:08:23.480
not just you personally.

00:08:23.480 --> 00:08:25.440
The patient becomes some aspect

00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:27.000
of the collective psyche

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:30.000
that something was using my sessions

00:08:30.120 --> 00:08:32.880
to bring about some catharsis

00:08:32.880 --> 00:08:34.960
in some small portion

00:08:34.960 --> 00:08:36.760
of the collective psyche,

00:08:36.760 --> 00:08:39.720
in order to drain the trauma

00:08:39.720 --> 00:08:42.320
that still resides within the psyche

00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:43.880
from human history.

00:08:43.880 --> 00:08:45.680
All the wars that we've been through,

00:08:45.680 --> 00:08:47.280
all the droughts, all the pain

00:08:47.280 --> 00:08:48.000
and suffering,

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:49.960
all the violence to each other,

00:08:49.960 --> 00:08:52.320
anything which is not resolved

00:08:52.320 --> 00:08:52.880
by the time

00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:55.720
the individuals who experience it die.

00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:59.720
That pain can, quite congeals

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:01.680
in the collective psyche

00:09:01.680 --> 00:09:02.880
and becomes a burden

00:09:02.880 --> 00:09:04.200
to the collective psyche.

00:09:04.200 --> 00:09:05.200
Healthy functioning.

00:09:06.240 --> 00:09:08.080
So that's the

00:09:08.080 --> 00:09:08.880
that's the the

00:09:08.880 --> 00:09:10.360
theory that I presented in

00:09:10.360 --> 00:09:12.760
Dark Net early Dawn.

00:09:12.760 --> 00:09:15.400
And what role do you feel

00:09:15.400 --> 00:09:18.400
healing individuals suffering may

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:19.800
or may play

00:09:19.800 --> 00:09:21.480
in the bigger picture of the cosmos,

00:09:21.480 --> 00:09:23.640
do you think?

00:09:23.640 --> 00:09:25.680
Well, I think all of us essentially

00:09:25.680 --> 00:09:27.680
are cells within the macro

00:09:27.680 --> 00:09:29.120
intelligence, the macro

00:09:29.120 --> 00:09:31.640
consciousness of our species.

00:09:31.640 --> 00:09:34.920
And so any time one individual

00:09:35.880 --> 00:09:37.280
comes to a healing,

00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:38.880
goes through a healing process

00:09:38.880 --> 00:09:39.720
and engages

00:09:39.720 --> 00:09:42.080
some aspect of their personal shadow,

00:09:42.080 --> 00:09:43.960
personal history,

00:09:43.960 --> 00:09:46.560
I think that sets in motion,

00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:48.920
a healing that radiates around the person

00:09:48.920 --> 00:09:51.320
360 degrees.

00:09:51.320 --> 00:09:52.920
So we are all fractal

00:09:52.920 --> 00:09:55.200
embedded in this larger

00:09:55.200 --> 00:09:58.200
collective mind, this collective psyche,

00:09:58.280 --> 00:10:01.080
so that when we work intensely,

00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:02.640
that healing

00:10:02.640 --> 00:10:03.480
doesn't just stay

00:10:03.480 --> 00:10:05.920
within our personal boundaries,

00:10:05.920 --> 00:10:08.880
but it naturally radiates out and touches

00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:10.760
the healing of the entire species

00:10:10.760 --> 00:10:12.280
to some degree.

00:10:12.280 --> 00:10:15.120
And so if you actually work

00:10:15.120 --> 00:10:16.480
and you're experiencing

00:10:16.480 --> 00:10:17.920
collective suffering

00:10:17.920 --> 00:10:19.320
and collective healing,

00:10:19.320 --> 00:10:22.200
that's just taking that one step farther.

00:10:22.200 --> 00:10:23.920
But anytime one of us

00:10:25.080 --> 00:10:25.920
addresses,

00:10:25.920 --> 00:10:28.920
confronts, and heals personal trauma,

00:10:29.080 --> 00:10:30.400
then that has a positive,

00:10:30.400 --> 00:10:31.400
uplifting effect

00:10:31.400 --> 00:10:34.400
on the collective psyche as a whole.

00:10:34.840 --> 00:10:36.200
It makes a lot of sense.

00:10:36.200 --> 00:10:37.800
And something else

00:10:37.800 --> 00:10:40.600
I was curious to ask, you know, is like

00:10:40.600 --> 00:10:42.000
you had to do this at a time

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:44.160
when psychedelics were were illegal

00:10:44.160 --> 00:10:46.440
so very much in the dark.

00:10:46.440 --> 00:10:48.320
What was it like to sort of

00:10:48.320 --> 00:10:50.520
go between these two worlds

00:10:50.520 --> 00:10:52.960
on a regular basis, where you are,

00:10:52.960 --> 00:10:54.640
you know, engaging with the sublime

00:10:54.640 --> 00:10:56.240
and then coming back to the mundane?

00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:58.880
What's what's that like as a person?

00:10:58.880 --> 00:11:00.160
Yeah.

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:01.800
Well, there are two aspects.

00:11:01.800 --> 00:11:03.240
One of them is engaging,

00:11:03.240 --> 00:11:04.680
as you say, the sublime.

00:11:04.680 --> 00:11:06.640
And coming back to the mundane.

00:11:06.640 --> 00:11:09.640
But the other aspect was,

00:11:09.800 --> 00:11:11.680
being a university professor

00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:13.200
teaching and doing the things

00:11:13.200 --> 00:11:14.760
professors do,

00:11:14.760 --> 00:11:15.720
but not being able

00:11:15.720 --> 00:11:16.960
to talk about my work

00:11:16.960 --> 00:11:19.480
to my colleagues or my, students.

00:11:19.480 --> 00:11:20.560
Never my students.

00:11:20.560 --> 00:11:22.080
Some of my colleagues knew what

00:11:22.080 --> 00:11:23.280
I was doing, and we talked,

00:11:25.120 --> 00:11:27.480
but not at great depth because,

00:11:27.480 --> 00:11:28.600
you know, for people

00:11:28.600 --> 00:11:30.360
who don't have deep experience

00:11:30.360 --> 00:11:31.280
with psychedelics,

00:11:31.280 --> 00:11:32.880
they simply can't understand.

00:11:32.880 --> 00:11:33.720
They can't follow.

00:11:33.720 --> 00:11:34.360
What happens

00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:35.200
when you take

00:11:35.200 --> 00:11:38.200
a deep journey into that work.

00:11:38.520 --> 00:11:40.320
So it was a secrecy.

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:42.240
I mean, I knew I had to do this

00:11:42.240 --> 00:11:43.960
in secret in order to do it,

00:11:43.960 --> 00:11:47.600
because by 1978 79, this was illegal.

00:11:48.360 --> 00:11:49.800
And I don't like breaking the law,

00:11:49.800 --> 00:11:52.440
but I felt that it was more important

00:11:52.440 --> 00:11:54.120
for me to use these substances,

00:11:54.120 --> 00:11:55.040
which would one day,

00:11:55.040 --> 00:11:58.080
I knew, become legal, to do them

00:11:58.080 --> 00:12:01.080
in this underground fashion.

00:12:01.520 --> 00:12:04.520
I found in the beginning it was fine,

00:12:04.880 --> 00:12:05.720
but I found that

00:12:05.720 --> 00:12:07.680
the longer I did this work,

00:12:07.680 --> 00:12:10.680
the more burdensome this secrecy became.

00:12:11.280 --> 00:12:13.440
And I found that if you can't,

00:12:13.440 --> 00:12:14.360
if you create,

00:12:15.400 --> 00:12:17.760
a persona which doesn't reflect

00:12:17.760 --> 00:12:19.360
your full integrity,

00:12:19.360 --> 00:12:21.160
it sets in motion pressures

00:12:21.160 --> 00:12:23.880
within the psyche. It's like you.

00:12:23.880 --> 00:12:25.960
It starts on the outside.

00:12:25.960 --> 00:12:27.840
But then eventually that

00:12:27.840 --> 00:12:28.960
that discrepancy

00:12:28.960 --> 00:12:30.680
between who you really are

00:12:30.680 --> 00:12:32.400
and who you are pretending to be

00:12:32.400 --> 00:12:34.440
or who you're being socially,

00:12:34.440 --> 00:12:36.080
it begins to produce cracks

00:12:36.080 --> 00:12:37.320
within the human psyche.

00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:41.360
And I found that years down the road,

00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:43.640
it was becoming increasingly difficult

00:12:43.640 --> 00:12:47.000
for me to maintain that boundary between

00:12:47.520 --> 00:12:48.240
my private

00:12:48.240 --> 00:12:49.880
non psychedelic life

00:12:49.880 --> 00:12:52.080
and my personal psychedelic light.

00:12:52.080 --> 00:12:53.120
And that's what I'd say.

00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:54.680
It's became more difficult.

00:12:54.680 --> 00:12:57.360
It means,

00:12:57.360 --> 00:12:58.880
I'm a teacher.

00:12:58.880 --> 00:13:01.880
Students would ask me questions,

00:13:02.400 --> 00:13:03.280
which I could tell

00:13:03.280 --> 00:13:05.680
was very important to them,

00:13:05.680 --> 00:13:08.600
but I could only answer them

00:13:08.600 --> 00:13:11.800
deeply, adequately if I were drawing upon

00:13:11.800 --> 00:13:13.240
my psychedelic experience,

00:13:13.240 --> 00:13:14.040
which was an art

00:13:14.040 --> 00:13:16.280
which I was not allowed to do.

00:13:16.280 --> 00:13:17.480
And as a teacher,

00:13:17.480 --> 00:13:19.640
the desire to share knowledge

00:13:19.640 --> 00:13:20.520
and to teach

00:13:22.280 --> 00:13:23.880
that created a tension with me.

00:13:23.880 --> 00:13:25.120
Because I had knowledge

00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:27.560
I was not allowed to share.

00:13:27.560 --> 00:13:29.320
The second part that you're talking about

00:13:29.320 --> 00:13:30.120
is the challenge

00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:33.120
of going into deep, transcendent states

00:13:33.120 --> 00:13:34.800
and then coming back to your ordinary,

00:13:34.800 --> 00:13:36.240
mundane condition

00:13:36.240 --> 00:13:37.520
and then going back again

00:13:37.520 --> 00:13:39.480
into deep, transcendent states

00:13:39.480 --> 00:13:40.320
and coming back

00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:42.480
into your ordinary condition.

00:13:42.480 --> 00:13:44.560
I want to say that

00:13:44.560 --> 00:13:46.960
I didn't have any difficulty

00:13:46.960 --> 00:13:49.000
psychologically, personally,

00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:50.520
going out and coming back.

00:13:50.520 --> 00:13:53.240
I seem to have a psyche.

00:13:53.240 --> 00:13:54.600
Not everybody does.

00:13:54.600 --> 00:13:57.360
But my system seemed to be comfortable

00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:58.760
losing its boundaries,

00:13:58.760 --> 00:14:01.480
opening up into transcendental spaces,

00:14:01.480 --> 00:14:02.520
and then coming back

00:14:02.520 --> 00:14:05.520
and congealing into my mundane space.

00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:07.240
And I would.

00:14:07.240 --> 00:14:10.120
I made a serious effort to recall

00:14:10.120 --> 00:14:10.960
and remember

00:14:10.960 --> 00:14:12.280
everything that happened to me

00:14:12.280 --> 00:14:13.000
in those states.

00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:14.520
So I would write my sessions up

00:14:14.520 --> 00:14:16.320
within 24 hours

00:14:16.320 --> 00:14:19.320
and I'd hold them, capture them.

00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:21.720
I tried to live by the teachings

00:14:21.720 --> 00:14:23.520
that were given to me.

00:14:23.520 --> 00:14:25.480
I tried to understand

00:14:25.480 --> 00:14:27.040
and comprehend things

00:14:27.040 --> 00:14:28.840
that were not comprehensible

00:14:28.840 --> 00:14:30.880
to me in the first stages.

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:32.320
But if you go back over

00:14:32.320 --> 00:14:33.800
and over and over again,

00:14:33.800 --> 00:14:35.560
then they begin to make more sense.

00:14:35.560 --> 00:14:37.240
You begin to be more comfortable at

00:14:37.240 --> 00:14:37.920
these states.

00:14:39.320 --> 00:14:40.920
But in the end, I mean, as I

00:14:40.920 --> 00:14:41.520
went into

00:14:41.520 --> 00:14:43.000
the late stages of the work

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:45.360
in the last five years of the work,

00:14:45.360 --> 00:14:47.800
I did find it difficult

00:14:47.800 --> 00:14:50.040
to come back into ordinary,

00:14:50.040 --> 00:14:51.920
mundane reality,

00:14:51.920 --> 00:14:54.600
because at that time I was being drawn

00:14:54.600 --> 00:14:57.600
so deeply into the divine

00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:01.320
body of crystalline consciousness,

00:15:01.320 --> 00:15:02.440
into what I call diamond

00:15:02.440 --> 00:15:03.920
consciousness,

00:15:03.920 --> 00:15:07.440
so deeply into those realities that,

00:15:08.320 --> 00:15:10.520
it just became very, very difficult

00:15:10.520 --> 00:15:12.440
to come out of those states

00:15:12.440 --> 00:15:14.120
and to come back into a state

00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:15.440
where I could remember them,

00:15:15.440 --> 00:15:17.840
and I could understand them,

00:15:17.840 --> 00:15:19.680
but I couldn't access them again

00:15:19.680 --> 00:15:21.120
under my own

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:24.120
power, within my own human resources.

00:15:24.680 --> 00:15:27.680
That became a burden.

00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.040
And it

00:15:29.040 --> 00:15:30.960
I didn't realize how much of a burden

00:15:30.960 --> 00:15:31.480
it would be.

00:15:31.480 --> 00:15:34.520
It became until after I stopped my work.

00:15:35.160 --> 00:15:36.000
It was after

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:38.400
I stopped my work that I realized

00:15:38.400 --> 00:15:39.360
that I really was kind

00:15:39.360 --> 00:15:42.360
of overextended, transcendental,

00:15:42.360 --> 00:15:44.440
and I had to make a conscious choice

00:15:44.440 --> 00:15:45.920
to stay grounded

00:15:45.920 --> 00:15:49.680
in time and space in my personal reality

00:15:50.400 --> 00:15:51.120
and integrate

00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:54.120
what I had done, rather than continue

00:15:54.200 --> 00:15:57.800
to go deep diving into the universe.

00:15:59.160 --> 00:16:00.200
Wow, wow.

00:16:00.200 --> 00:16:03.200
And.

00:16:04.960 --> 00:16:06.120
Was the conclusion

00:16:06.120 --> 00:16:09.120
that you took from that that.

00:16:10.240 --> 00:16:10.840
There was a

00:16:10.840 --> 00:16:12.280
there was a meaning to be found,

00:16:12.280 --> 00:16:15.000
a purpose to be found for your life in

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:16.440
bringing the transcendent

00:16:16.440 --> 00:16:19.440
to the everyday.

00:16:20.160 --> 00:16:22.280
There was in several ways.

00:16:22.280 --> 00:16:25.280
First, again, I'm not a therapist.

00:16:25.440 --> 00:16:27.240
I'm not trained as a therapist.

00:16:27.240 --> 00:16:29.880
And I made the decision long ago to

00:16:29.880 --> 00:16:31.960
to not become a therapist either,

00:16:31.960 --> 00:16:32.840
even in the back

00:16:32.840 --> 00:16:35.000
in the underground sense,

00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:37.920
but to function as a solo explorer,

00:16:37.920 --> 00:16:40.560
to try to be willing to push my system

00:16:40.560 --> 00:16:42.120
as far as I could,

00:16:42.120 --> 00:16:44.040
to go out as deeply as I could,

00:16:44.040 --> 00:16:45.440
and to try to understand

00:16:45.440 --> 00:16:47.080
what I was being shown,

00:16:47.080 --> 00:16:49.080
in those conditions.

00:16:49.080 --> 00:16:51.720
So that satisfied a very deep

00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:54.080
philosophical need to understand.

00:16:54.080 --> 00:16:57.320
And as I have come to understand

00:16:57.320 --> 00:16:58.320
my past lives,

00:16:58.320 --> 00:16:58.760
I've done

00:16:58.760 --> 00:17:01.200
several years of past life therapy.

00:17:01.200 --> 00:17:02.760
I've uncovered a dozen

00:17:02.760 --> 00:17:04.280
or so of my former lives,

00:17:05.520 --> 00:17:07.000
and I began to understand

00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:08.680
that some of the experiences

00:17:08.680 --> 00:17:11.680
and some of the lack of understanding

00:17:11.920 --> 00:17:14.640
of how reality functions

00:17:14.640 --> 00:17:17.640
was transferred into this incarnation

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:20.760
and and seeding my deep desire

00:17:20.760 --> 00:17:23.400
to understand how the world works.

00:17:23.400 --> 00:17:25.680
Why is there so much suffering?

00:17:25.680 --> 00:17:27.800
How can a benign

00:17:27.800 --> 00:17:30.560
and supremely intelligent

00:17:30.560 --> 00:17:32.240
source manifest

00:17:32.240 --> 00:17:33.960
a universe that is so painful

00:17:33.960 --> 00:17:35.320
and so difficult?

00:17:35.320 --> 00:17:36.760
What's going on here?

00:17:36.760 --> 00:17:38.800
Why is it this way?

00:17:38.800 --> 00:17:41.240
Have we done something wrong?

00:17:41.240 --> 00:17:43.520
Why is this difficult?

00:17:43.520 --> 00:17:44.960
And now I think I have

00:17:44.960 --> 00:17:46.240
an understanding of that.

00:17:46.240 --> 00:17:48.280
And that

00:17:48.280 --> 00:17:51.280
that was a primary drive to understand.

00:17:51.480 --> 00:17:52.960
And then the second drive

00:17:52.960 --> 00:17:55.560
is to share that understanding.

00:17:55.560 --> 00:17:56.520
But I wasn't really

00:17:56.520 --> 00:17:57.560
and I did share that

00:17:57.560 --> 00:17:59.560
understanding indirectly

00:17:59.560 --> 00:18:01.160
in the courses that I was teaching

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:02.520
at the university,

00:18:02.520 --> 00:18:04.040
courses in world religions,

00:18:04.040 --> 00:18:06.040
eastern religions, Buddhism,

00:18:06.040 --> 00:18:08.240
comparative mysticism.

00:18:08.240 --> 00:18:10.800
But I wasn't able to share them directly

00:18:10.800 --> 00:18:11.560
as coming

00:18:11.560 --> 00:18:13.120
from these psychedelic visions

00:18:13.120 --> 00:18:15.600
until after I retired

00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:17.760
and after I began to write

00:18:17.760 --> 00:18:19.720
completely uninhibited Lee,

00:18:19.720 --> 00:18:21.040
which I did in,

00:18:22.440 --> 00:18:24.280
LSD in the mind of the universe.

00:18:24.280 --> 00:18:26.040
And when I began to do that

00:18:26.040 --> 00:18:29.040
and began to follow that into the world,

00:18:29.320 --> 00:18:31.800
the split that I created in myself

00:18:31.800 --> 00:18:33.440
between the professor part

00:18:33.440 --> 00:18:35.160
and the psychedelic part

00:18:35.160 --> 00:18:36.280
began to heal,

00:18:36.280 --> 00:18:38.400
and they began to be merged,

00:18:38.400 --> 00:18:39.320
until finally,

00:18:39.320 --> 00:18:40.440
I can be my full

00:18:40.440 --> 00:18:43.440
and complete self in all circumstance.

00:18:44.280 --> 00:18:45.400
And what was that like?

00:18:45.400 --> 00:18:46.880
Whenever you were able to sort of

00:18:46.880 --> 00:18:48.120
let your mind off a leash

00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:49.120
and just actually write

00:18:49.120 --> 00:18:49.920
about these topics

00:18:49.920 --> 00:18:50.760
that had been

00:18:50.760 --> 00:18:52.080
swirling around up there

00:18:52.080 --> 00:18:55.080
for, for decades?

00:18:55.720 --> 00:18:57.920
Well,

00:18:57.920 --> 00:18:59.240
it was healing first.

00:18:59.240 --> 00:19:00.120
It was a little scary.

00:19:00.120 --> 00:19:03.120
I mean, it literally after I retired,

00:19:03.360 --> 00:19:06.440
it took me three years to get myself

00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:08.320
in a psychological space

00:19:08.320 --> 00:19:09.160
where I was willing

00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:11.760
to share this information because I,

00:19:11.760 --> 00:19:12.840
I knew

00:19:12.840 --> 00:19:13.680
my colleagues

00:19:13.680 --> 00:19:15.240
would not be able to understand it

00:19:15.240 --> 00:19:16.240
or take it in.

00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:17.320
I knew I was writing

00:19:17.320 --> 00:19:18.680
for the next generation,

00:19:18.680 --> 00:19:21.600
younger people who would be coming along.

00:19:21.600 --> 00:19:25.120
But even so, to share your deepest,

00:19:25.320 --> 00:19:28.160
most intimate spiritual experiences

00:19:28.160 --> 00:19:29.000
with the world,

00:19:29.960 --> 00:19:30.640
you know, that's like

00:19:30.640 --> 00:19:32.000
sharing your sex life.

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:34.320
And it's very, very private.

00:19:34.320 --> 00:19:35.320
And it took me a while

00:19:35.320 --> 00:19:36.000
to be willing

00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:39.160
to let people that deeply into my life,

00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:42.160
because I'm a private person by nature.

00:19:42.680 --> 00:19:45.480
And eventually I came to this position

00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:48.360
of being willing to let people in.

00:19:48.360 --> 00:19:51.360
I really, by understanding that

00:19:51.520 --> 00:19:53.080
these experiences

00:19:53.080 --> 00:19:55.840
were not given to me for myself,

00:19:55.840 --> 00:19:56.880
they were given to me

00:19:56.880 --> 00:19:59.800
to pass along to others, to support them

00:19:59.800 --> 00:20:01.360
in their spiritual journey

00:20:01.360 --> 00:20:03.840
and their explorations in life.

00:20:03.840 --> 00:20:06.160
And so I, I surrendered

00:20:06.160 --> 00:20:09.160
personal attachment to the story

00:20:09.520 --> 00:20:11.400
and then began the process

00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:12.360
of telling the story.

00:20:12.360 --> 00:20:13.600
It took me

00:20:13.600 --> 00:20:15.160
five years to write

00:20:15.160 --> 00:20:16.920
LSD in the mind of the universe.

00:20:16.920 --> 00:20:18.600
And the last chapter,

00:20:18.600 --> 00:20:19.720
which is about coming

00:20:19.720 --> 00:20:21.400
and coming down the mountain.

00:20:21.400 --> 00:20:21.880
When I

00:20:21.880 --> 00:20:22.560
what happened

00:20:22.560 --> 00:20:23.520
after I stopped

00:20:23.520 --> 00:20:24.960
my sessions

00:20:24.960 --> 00:20:26.760
was the longest chapter to write.

00:20:26.760 --> 00:20:28.200
It took me an entire year

00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:30.360
just to write that one chapter,

00:20:30.360 --> 00:20:31.080
because I really,

00:20:32.200 --> 00:20:32.680
I really

00:20:32.680 --> 00:20:34.320
had to process

00:20:34.320 --> 00:20:36.600
everything that had happened to me

00:20:36.600 --> 00:20:38.920
in the 20 years

00:20:38.920 --> 00:20:41.520
after I'd stopped my sessions.

00:20:41.520 --> 00:20:43.840
So once I did this, once

00:20:43.840 --> 00:20:45.280
I went through this process,

00:20:45.280 --> 00:20:48.280
once I had told the story,

00:20:49.280 --> 00:20:50.040
it felt good.

00:20:50.040 --> 00:20:51.800
It felt good to come out of the closet,

00:20:51.800 --> 00:20:54.800
because being in a psychedelic closet

00:20:54.800 --> 00:20:56.120
is just as damaging

00:20:56.120 --> 00:20:58.000
as being in any other closet

00:20:58.000 --> 00:20:59.560
where you have to deny something.

00:20:59.560 --> 00:21:02.520
It's important to you.

00:21:02.520 --> 00:21:04.440
For sure, for sure.

00:21:04.440 --> 00:21:06.520
And

00:21:06.520 --> 00:21:09.520
for in your,

00:21:09.680 --> 00:21:10.840
a few things come to mind here.

00:21:10.840 --> 00:21:13.800
But for me.

00:21:13.800 --> 00:21:15.840
Any time in my life

00:21:15.840 --> 00:21:18.000
when I've turned toward suffering

00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:19.480
and engage

00:21:19.480 --> 00:21:22.480
with suffering and seek to alleviate it,

00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:26.000
the experience is always meaningful.

00:21:26.600 --> 00:21:27.840
It always

00:21:27.840 --> 00:21:30.760
touches something deep inside that

00:21:30.760 --> 00:21:31.040
you.

00:21:31.040 --> 00:21:32.360
I wouldn't say it feels good,

00:21:32.360 --> 00:21:33.720
but it feels right

00:21:33.720 --> 00:21:35.640
if it's whole, you know.

00:21:35.640 --> 00:21:36.280
And I was wondering

00:21:36.280 --> 00:21:37.480
you did mentioned there about,

00:21:37.480 --> 00:21:39.080
you know, you've you've really

00:21:39.080 --> 00:21:39.840
you got the answers

00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:40.600
you were looking for

00:21:40.600 --> 00:21:42.720
with regards to suffering.

00:21:42.720 --> 00:21:44.080
Would you be able to just to comment

00:21:44.080 --> 00:21:46.920
on that and expand on that a little and

00:21:46.920 --> 00:21:47.840
share your thoughts, your.

00:21:49.720 --> 00:21:51.000
Well, first, just an

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:54.000
observation on the process.

00:21:55.720 --> 00:21:58.800
When you are confronted with suffering

00:21:59.000 --> 00:22:00.440
in psychedelic space,

00:22:00.440 --> 00:22:03.440
as in psychotherapeutic space,

00:22:03.720 --> 00:22:05.480
it's challenging, it's difficult.

00:22:05.480 --> 00:22:06.160
It's difficult

00:22:06.160 --> 00:22:08.560
to let that much suffering in.

00:22:08.560 --> 00:22:10.760
But as you say, it may not be fun,

00:22:10.760 --> 00:22:11.880
may not be pleasant,

00:22:11.880 --> 00:22:14.640
but it feels like the right thing to do.

00:22:14.640 --> 00:22:15.840
And when you

00:22:15.840 --> 00:22:18.840
embrace your personal shadow suffering,

00:22:19.440 --> 00:22:22.440
there comes a point where eventually,

00:22:22.520 --> 00:22:24.720
once you integrate it all and you,

00:22:24.720 --> 00:22:25.520
you see what

00:22:25.520 --> 00:22:26.520
the source is

00:22:26.520 --> 00:22:29.440
and you confront it and you live with it,

00:22:29.440 --> 00:22:31.200
there is a certain falling away.

00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:33.560
You know, the pain falls away

00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:35.240
and there is a freedom

00:22:35.240 --> 00:22:38.160
which unfolds in its wake.

00:22:38.160 --> 00:22:41.160
And I found that to be true also

00:22:41.160 --> 00:22:43.080
for all the forms of suffering

00:22:43.080 --> 00:22:44.920
that surfaced on this journey,

00:22:44.920 --> 00:22:47.000
even when I was going through

00:22:47.000 --> 00:22:49.040
that terrible collective suffering,

00:22:49.040 --> 00:22:51.120
the hell the hell realms, you might say,

00:22:52.120 --> 00:22:53.680
and I felt that there

00:22:53.680 --> 00:22:55.240
was a meaning to this work,

00:22:55.240 --> 00:22:57.560
even though it wasn't personal meaning

00:22:57.560 --> 00:22:58.800
it was

00:22:58.800 --> 00:23:01.640
personal in the sense that it felt like

00:23:01.640 --> 00:23:03.960
this is something that I was meant to do.

00:23:03.960 --> 00:23:06.600
And as I learned later down the road,

00:23:06.600 --> 00:23:09.240
that was true, that that,

00:23:09.240 --> 00:23:10.880
as I began to understand

00:23:10.880 --> 00:23:12.520
and was shown my purpose

00:23:12.520 --> 00:23:14.320
for this incarnation,

00:23:14.320 --> 00:23:15.960
a very significant part of

00:23:15.960 --> 00:23:17.880
it was this actual

00:23:17.880 --> 00:23:19.560
process of facilitating

00:23:19.560 --> 00:23:21.520
collective healing.

00:23:21.520 --> 00:23:24.960
When I went into this pain

00:23:24.960 --> 00:23:26.880
and allowed it to run through me

00:23:26.880 --> 00:23:28.440
deeper and deeper.

00:23:28.440 --> 00:23:31.440
Eventually, after two years,

00:23:31.600 --> 00:23:32.920
it culminated in a

00:23:32.920 --> 00:23:35.920
in a crescendo of of pain.

00:23:36.240 --> 00:23:37.040
And then it sort of

00:23:37.040 --> 00:23:39.360
spun me out into deep,

00:23:39.360 --> 00:23:40.720
transpersonal places.

00:23:40.720 --> 00:23:42.240
It's when it spun me out

00:23:42.240 --> 00:23:43.960
beyond the entire

00:23:43.960 --> 00:23:46.960
human psyche into archetypal reality.

00:23:47.760 --> 00:23:49.680
And there were still episodes of

00:23:49.680 --> 00:23:52.120
of suffering remaining, because

00:23:53.120 --> 00:23:54.600
what I found is that

00:23:54.600 --> 00:23:57.600
death and rebirth is a cycle,

00:23:57.720 --> 00:24:00.720
you know, it just it goes round and round

00:24:00.840 --> 00:24:03.720
and you don't die once when you simply

00:24:03.720 --> 00:24:05.560
when you die at the egoic level,

00:24:05.560 --> 00:24:06.840
that gives you access

00:24:06.840 --> 00:24:07.880
to a certain level

00:24:07.880 --> 00:24:10.800
of transpersonal consciousness.

00:24:10.800 --> 00:24:12.960
But if you keep pushing,

00:24:12.960 --> 00:24:14.160
then eventually you're

00:24:14.160 --> 00:24:16.320
going to come to a threshold

00:24:16.320 --> 00:24:17.440
and you'll have to go through

00:24:17.440 --> 00:24:19.160
another round of dying,

00:24:19.160 --> 00:24:20.960
another round of suffering

00:24:20.960 --> 00:24:21.480
in order

00:24:21.480 --> 00:24:22.400
to gain access

00:24:22.400 --> 00:24:24.840
to the next level of consciousness.

00:24:24.840 --> 00:24:27.360
And if you're systematically systematic

00:24:27.360 --> 00:24:29.120
and you work at that level,

00:24:29.120 --> 00:24:30.840
eventually the same thing will happen.

00:24:30.840 --> 00:24:31.680
You'll go to yet

00:24:31.680 --> 00:24:33.920
another round of death and rebirth,

00:24:33.920 --> 00:24:35.280
and that'll take you into yet

00:24:35.280 --> 00:24:37.200
another level of consciousness

00:24:37.200 --> 00:24:39.240
where the rules of physics are different.

00:24:39.240 --> 00:24:40.480
The rules are just different.

00:24:40.480 --> 00:24:41.720
It's a different realm.

00:24:43.200 --> 00:24:46.200
I found that,

00:24:47.560 --> 00:24:49.560
I learned to trust that process,

00:24:49.560 --> 00:24:50.920
to trust the process,

00:24:50.920 --> 00:24:53.160
that welcoming anything that happens,

00:24:53.160 --> 00:24:53.640
no matter

00:24:53.640 --> 00:24:55.560
whether you understand it or not.

00:24:55.560 --> 00:24:58.040
Embracing the suffering that happens

00:24:58.040 --> 00:25:00.000
always work to my betterment

00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:00.360
in work,

00:25:00.360 --> 00:25:02.360
to the betterment of

00:25:02.360 --> 00:25:05.160
beings that I'll never meet.

00:25:05.160 --> 00:25:06.040
But it also worked to

00:25:06.040 --> 00:25:07.160
my personal betterment

00:25:07.160 --> 00:25:08.200
because it allowed me

00:25:08.200 --> 00:25:10.440
to experience things

00:25:10.440 --> 00:25:11.560
that were important to me

00:25:11.560 --> 00:25:13.920
that became important to me.

00:25:13.920 --> 00:25:16.920
That kind of ontological intimacy

00:25:17.160 --> 00:25:19.680
with the creative principle of existence

00:25:19.680 --> 00:25:22.680
was really important.

00:25:22.800 --> 00:25:25.240
How is your inner experience of life

00:25:25.240 --> 00:25:28.240
now different

00:25:28.560 --> 00:25:30.760
after you've did this work

00:25:30.760 --> 00:25:31.920
compared to before?

00:25:31.920 --> 00:25:33.040
I know it's very difficult

00:25:33.040 --> 00:25:34.800
to put your own

00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:35.840
your own perceptions

00:25:35.840 --> 00:25:36.720
into into words,

00:25:36.720 --> 00:25:38.240
but is there anything you could share

00:25:38.240 --> 00:25:39.880
there about

00:25:39.880 --> 00:25:42.160
what life is like for you on the inside?

00:25:42.160 --> 00:25:43.800
After having been through

00:25:43.800 --> 00:25:46.680
such such incredible experiences?

00:25:49.040 --> 00:25:50.240
Well,

00:25:50.240 --> 00:25:51.480
I don't consider myself

00:25:51.480 --> 00:25:53.280
an enlightened being.

00:25:53.280 --> 00:25:55.560
So let's just get that out of the way.

00:25:55.560 --> 00:25:57.840
I don't live in that kind of space.

00:25:57.840 --> 00:25:59.600
I think

00:25:59.600 --> 00:26:01.440
if I were seeking enlightenment

00:26:01.440 --> 00:26:02.160
in this work,

00:26:02.160 --> 00:26:03.800
I would have done it very differently.

00:26:03.800 --> 00:26:06.480
I would have done much lower doses,

00:26:06.480 --> 00:26:08.080
you know,

00:26:08.080 --> 00:26:09.760
enlightenment, as I understand it,

00:26:09.760 --> 00:26:12.440
as a condition of transparency

00:26:12.440 --> 00:26:14.280
to the ground of reality,

00:26:14.280 --> 00:26:15.480
which is always present,

00:26:15.480 --> 00:26:18.040
never changing, always there

00:26:18.040 --> 00:26:19.640
living in communion,

00:26:19.640 --> 00:26:20.600
daily communion,

00:26:20.600 --> 00:26:23.600
and minute by minute with this reality.

00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:26.800
And while I certainly touched things

00:26:26.800 --> 00:26:29.800
like that, my work really was different.

00:26:30.200 --> 00:26:32.280
It wasn't therapeutic healing

00:26:32.280 --> 00:26:34.280
and it wasn't aimed primarily

00:26:34.280 --> 00:26:36.880
at spiritual awakening.

00:26:36.880 --> 00:26:38.760
I began to understand that it was aimed

00:26:38.760 --> 00:26:41.040
at cosmological exploration.

00:26:41.040 --> 00:26:43.680
I was trying to seek and understand

00:26:43.680 --> 00:26:44.880
larger and larger

00:26:44.880 --> 00:26:47.240
pictures of how the universe works.

00:26:48.640 --> 00:26:50.120
So the end result,

00:26:50.120 --> 00:26:53.120
once you do that, is.

00:26:54.720 --> 00:26:57.080
It leaves you with a certain porosity,

00:26:57.080 --> 00:26:59.400
but not the same type of porosity

00:26:59.400 --> 00:27:00.640
that is enlightenment.

00:27:00.640 --> 00:27:02.920
Classically said,

00:27:02.920 --> 00:27:05.120
it has left me,

00:27:05.120 --> 00:27:08.040
calmer, more at peace.

00:27:08.040 --> 00:27:11.280
I understand reality more than I did

00:27:11.280 --> 00:27:13.600
before. More deeply.

00:27:13.600 --> 00:27:16.680
I understand reincarnation more deeply.

00:27:16.680 --> 00:27:19.680
I have an understanding of

00:27:20.160 --> 00:27:23.120
the cosmic processes that are involved

00:27:23.120 --> 00:27:24.960
in human evolution,

00:27:24.960 --> 00:27:27.800
where evolution is taking humanity,

00:27:27.800 --> 00:27:31.560
where reincarnation is taking humanity.

00:27:32.280 --> 00:27:35.800
There is a certain step back and enjoying

00:27:36.480 --> 00:27:39.160
the magnificent splendor

00:27:39.160 --> 00:27:42.120
of the universe around us, and also

00:27:42.120 --> 00:27:44.000
understanding with empathy,

00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:45.600
with compassion,

00:27:45.600 --> 00:27:48.600
the suffering that people go through,

00:27:49.040 --> 00:27:52.040
so much and.

00:27:52.440 --> 00:27:54.360
I have a certain understanding

00:27:54.360 --> 00:27:57.680
of how that plays out

00:27:58.440 --> 00:28:01.440
in a larger evolutionary horizon.

00:28:02.200 --> 00:28:06.320
So there there is a, a contentment.

00:28:07.480 --> 00:28:08.880
There's, certainly

00:28:08.880 --> 00:28:11.880
a deepened compassion.

00:28:13.960 --> 00:28:16.760
An understanding,

00:28:16.760 --> 00:28:19.760
a relaxation,

00:28:21.520 --> 00:28:23.400
and a desire to be of use

00:28:23.400 --> 00:28:25.440
as to be just to be helpful,

00:28:25.440 --> 00:28:28.320
just to be as much use to other people

00:28:28.320 --> 00:28:31.320
as I can in the time that's left to me.

00:28:32.400 --> 00:28:34.800
That sounds pretty good.

00:28:34.800 --> 00:28:37.600
Do you fear death?

00:28:37.600 --> 00:28:38.520
No, I don't.

00:28:38.520 --> 00:28:41.000
Not at all. I look forward to it.

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:42.720
I don't look forward to the act of dying.

00:28:42.720 --> 00:28:43.680
But I look forward to

00:28:43.680 --> 00:28:45.360
what's on the other side.

00:28:45.360 --> 00:28:46.880
And I'll mention in this context

00:28:46.880 --> 00:28:49.560
that my partner, my partner of 25 years,

00:28:49.560 --> 00:28:52.800
Christina Hardy, she died last spring.

00:28:53.560 --> 00:28:55.440
She was a psychic, not like myself.

00:28:55.440 --> 00:28:58.120
She had had many deep experiences.

00:28:58.120 --> 00:29:00.040
She had no fear of death.

00:29:00.040 --> 00:29:02.520
And the two of us have no fear of death

00:29:02.520 --> 00:29:03.800
because she had gone

00:29:03.800 --> 00:29:05.160
to where she would be going

00:29:05.160 --> 00:29:06.240
when she died.

00:29:06.240 --> 00:29:08.280
She had personal familiarity with it,

00:29:08.280 --> 00:29:09.520
and she knew

00:29:09.520 --> 00:29:11.640
that it was a place of great blessing,

00:29:11.640 --> 00:29:14.280
great beauty, great joy.

00:29:14.280 --> 00:29:17.520
And when you when you understand,

00:29:17.760 --> 00:29:18.920
I mean, and I don't mean

00:29:18.920 --> 00:29:22.040
just intellectually, but understand and,

00:29:22.680 --> 00:29:25.240
had deep communion

00:29:25.240 --> 00:29:27.720
with these deeper levels of reality

00:29:27.720 --> 00:29:29.760
that on the other side of

00:29:29.760 --> 00:29:31.080
time, space, reality,

00:29:32.080 --> 00:29:35.080
then approaching death

00:29:35.280 --> 00:29:38.280
is not the dirge of sadness or mourning

00:29:38.280 --> 00:29:40.960
or just grief and loss,

00:29:40.960 --> 00:29:41.600
but rather

00:29:41.600 --> 00:29:43.440
it becomes a celebration of a life.

00:29:43.440 --> 00:29:44.760
Well lived.

00:29:44.760 --> 00:29:46.920
Christina had lived her life very well.

00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:47.640
She had risen

00:29:47.640 --> 00:29:49.720
to the challenges of her life,

00:29:49.720 --> 00:29:51.600
and her last years with me

00:29:51.600 --> 00:29:53.120
were some of the best years

00:29:53.120 --> 00:29:54.440
of our marriage.

00:29:54.440 --> 00:29:57.760
As we as we move towards her death.

00:29:59.080 --> 00:30:02.160
And I expect that to be true for me too.

00:30:02.160 --> 00:30:04.200
I don't have any fear of death

00:30:04.200 --> 00:30:07.200
in, In fact, I just have to be patient.

00:30:08.120 --> 00:30:11.320
Because for me, I my belief is

00:30:11.320 --> 00:30:12.360
my understanding

00:30:12.360 --> 00:30:16.200
is that at the very least, when I die,

00:30:16.200 --> 00:30:18.640
I'll be able to go back to

00:30:18.640 --> 00:30:20.880
some of the deepest places

00:30:20.880 --> 00:30:23.560
in the universe that I had access through

00:30:23.560 --> 00:30:25.080
my psychedelic work.

00:30:25.080 --> 00:30:27.040
Because I know the address

00:30:27.040 --> 00:30:28.920
as Robert Monroe would say,

00:30:28.920 --> 00:30:30.120
you can go anywhere

00:30:30.120 --> 00:30:31.440
where you know the address,

00:30:31.440 --> 00:30:33.800
and I know the address of these places,

00:30:33.800 --> 00:30:36.600
and I can go back to there, and I know

00:30:36.600 --> 00:30:37.560
I'll be able to go on

00:30:37.560 --> 00:30:39.720
even deeper from there.

00:30:39.720 --> 00:30:42.240
So, no, I have no fear of death.

00:30:42.240 --> 00:30:44.480
Adele. Wow. Okay.

00:30:45.680 --> 00:30:45.960
Yeah.

00:30:45.960 --> 00:30:46.960
I've heard you describe death

00:30:46.960 --> 00:30:48.800
almost as a as a homecoming,

00:30:48.800 --> 00:30:49.440
and that

00:30:49.440 --> 00:30:50.760
that's a really interesting way

00:30:50.760 --> 00:30:53.720
to where to put it.

00:30:53.720 --> 00:30:55.440
Can you tell us about the work of

00:30:55.440 --> 00:30:56.480
of Michael Newton?

00:30:56.480 --> 00:30:59.520
And to what extent do you believe that

00:31:00.960 --> 00:31:02.640
we before

00:31:02.640 --> 00:31:05.640
coming here, we consciously choose

00:31:05.960 --> 00:31:07.360
a particular life,

00:31:07.360 --> 00:31:10.360
a particular that's a cohort, a family,

00:31:10.480 --> 00:31:13.440
a people to come here with.

00:31:13.440 --> 00:31:14.040
What are you saying?

00:31:14.040 --> 00:31:17.000
What do you make of that idea?

00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:17.880
Well,

00:31:17.880 --> 00:31:18.680
I have found that

00:31:18.680 --> 00:31:20.600
to be true, in my experience,

00:31:20.600 --> 00:31:22.280
as I've come to know the deeper

00:31:22.280 --> 00:31:25.280
cause and effect patterns of my life.

00:31:26.200 --> 00:31:27.480
You know, my first book,

00:31:27.480 --> 00:31:30.440
Life Cycles, was on reincarnation,

00:31:30.440 --> 00:31:32.760
in which I tried to integrate

00:31:32.760 --> 00:31:34.440
all the best available evidence

00:31:34.440 --> 00:31:36.240
for reincarnation that was available.

00:31:36.240 --> 00:31:37.560
At the time.

00:31:37.560 --> 00:31:38.280
I did not know

00:31:38.280 --> 00:31:40.200
Michael Newton's work at that time.

00:31:40.200 --> 00:31:41.400
His came a little bit later.

00:31:42.800 --> 00:31:44.640
I like Michael Newton's work a lot.

00:31:44.640 --> 00:31:47.520
I respect his work a great deal.

00:31:47.520 --> 00:31:48.960
It rings true to me.

00:31:48.960 --> 00:31:50.080
It rings true

00:31:50.080 --> 00:31:51.480
to my own

00:31:51.480 --> 00:31:53.000
experience of the bardo

00:31:53.000 --> 00:31:54.680
in psychedelic states.

00:31:54.680 --> 00:31:57.320
It rings true to what I understand

00:31:57.320 --> 00:31:58.880
from the mystical traditions

00:31:58.880 --> 00:32:00.480
of the world, particularly Buddhism,

00:32:00.480 --> 00:32:01.440
and their description

00:32:01.440 --> 00:32:03.000
of what happens to an individual

00:32:03.000 --> 00:32:04.600
when they die.

00:32:04.600 --> 00:32:07.080
His is more detailed.

00:32:07.080 --> 00:32:09.760
Another person that I would mention,

00:32:09.760 --> 00:32:11.080
if you want to understand

00:32:11.080 --> 00:32:12.840
the deep structure of the cycle

00:32:12.840 --> 00:32:14.520
going into the spiritual reality,

00:32:14.520 --> 00:32:16.000
coming back to time and space

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:19.000
into the circle is,

00:32:19.040 --> 00:32:21.640
Robert Monroe.

00:32:21.640 --> 00:32:23.560
He wrote three important journey,

00:32:23.560 --> 00:32:25.560
books on the out-of-body state,

00:32:25.560 --> 00:32:27.440
his experiences out-of-body,

00:32:27.440 --> 00:32:29.400
and in his book Far Journeys

00:32:29.400 --> 00:32:31.240
and the Ultimate Journey, two books,

00:32:31.240 --> 00:32:33.360
Far Journeys and The Ultimate Journey,

00:32:33.360 --> 00:32:36.000
he gives a comprehensive description

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:38.160
of what happens to us when we die.

00:32:38.160 --> 00:32:41.120
And I find it very congruent with,

00:32:41.120 --> 00:32:42.480
Michael Newton's description

00:32:43.440 --> 00:32:44.040
now on the

00:32:44.040 --> 00:32:47.040
choosing of our incarnation.

00:32:47.360 --> 00:32:49.000
I'm an educator, so let me bring

00:32:49.000 --> 00:32:52.000
an educator's, metaphor to it.

00:32:52.680 --> 00:32:54.000
When children,

00:32:54.000 --> 00:32:55.600
are starting their studies,

00:32:55.600 --> 00:32:57.040
we don't give kindergartens

00:32:57.040 --> 00:32:58.440
and earnest and first graders

00:32:58.440 --> 00:33:00.120
much of a choice in what they study.

00:33:00.120 --> 00:33:02.120
We say study this,

00:33:02.120 --> 00:33:03.720
but as you go into high school,

00:33:03.720 --> 00:33:05.280
you have more choices,

00:33:05.280 --> 00:33:06.840
more freedom to choose

00:33:06.840 --> 00:33:08.040
as you go into college

00:33:08.040 --> 00:33:08.960
and graduate school,

00:33:08.960 --> 00:33:10.240
you have a lot more freedom

00:33:10.240 --> 00:33:12.560
to choose what you're going to study.

00:33:12.560 --> 00:33:13.920
And I think it's something like that

00:33:13.920 --> 00:33:15.560
for the soul, too.

00:33:15.560 --> 00:33:16.520
It may be the case

00:33:16.520 --> 00:33:19.480
that in the early stages, you basically

00:33:19.480 --> 00:33:22.480
things are arranged for you and you go,

00:33:22.600 --> 00:33:23.680
where you're told by

00:33:23.680 --> 00:33:26.480
people who understand more than you do.

00:33:26.480 --> 00:33:27.480
But as you grow

00:33:27.480 --> 00:33:28.840
and as you learn,

00:33:28.840 --> 00:33:31.280
I think you have more freedom and more,

00:33:31.280 --> 00:33:32.240
freedom to choose

00:33:32.240 --> 00:33:34.320
so that by the time you have

00:33:34.320 --> 00:33:36.960
enough cycles of reincarnation

00:33:36.960 --> 00:33:38.320
under your belt.

